fix(adapter): add fallthrough guard in tools JSON parsing (#136)
The tools JSON parsing block had three failure paths with no early return:
1. Empty content - if content.strip() skipped
2. JSONDecodeError - warning logged but no return
3. Missing tool_name - neither if/elif matched

All three fell through to output_model_class path which raised ValueError
when output_model_class was None (Router case).

Add fallthrough guard that returns {"tool_calls": []} when tools mode
fails to parse a valid tool call.

