2026-02-03 00:37:45 -0700
fix(exit-interview): clear max_iterations_exceeded flag unconditionally (#104)
The max_iterations_exceeded artifact is a signal TO Exit Interview. Once
processed, it has no meaning and must be cleared. Previously, the flag
persisted after Exit Interview, causing subsequent passes to see stale
True values and return INCOMPLETE even when tasks were objectively done.

This caused infinite retry loops: trace_0 hits max_iterations → Exit
Interview sees flag, returns INCOMPLETE but doesn't clear → trace_1
completes work → Exit Interview still sees stale flag → loops forever.

Fix: All 4 return paths in Exit Interview now unconditionally set
max_iterations_exceeded=False. The flag is consumed, not echoed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

