feat(exit-interview): add trace stutter detection via semantic-chunker MCP
Integrates semantic-chunker MCP service to detect when project_director
repeats the same operations across invocations without making progress.

Changes:
- docker-compose.yml: Add semantic-chunker-mcp service (profile: semantic-chunker)
- config.yaml: Add external_mcp.services entry + exit_interview tools config
- exit_interview_specialist.py: Add _detect_trace_stutter() using calculate_drift
- facilitator_specialist.py: Fix ACCUMULATE mode to always pass resume_trace
- docs/MCP_GUIDE.md: Update external services table

The stutter detection uses cosine distance between consecutive trace
serializations. Drift < 0.1 indicates repeated work, triggering ACCUMULATE
mode so the agent sees its prior traces and can try a different approach.

Graceful degradation: If semantic-chunker unavailable, stutter detection
becomes a no-op and workflow continues normally.

