feat(resilience): generalized cycle detection for tool stagnation (#78)
Adds cycle detection to catch repeating tool call patterns, not just
identical consecutive calls. This addresses batch operations where the
LLM loops through N files repeatedly without making progress.

Changes:
- Add cycle_detection.py with detect_cycle() and detect_cycle_with_pattern()
- Update react_mixin.py to use cycle detection instead of identity check
- Replace STAGNATION_THRESHOLD with CYCLE_MIN_REPETITIONS
- Add 17 unit tests for cycle detection edge cases

The algorithm finds the shortest repeating pattern at the end of the
tool call history. For example, [a,b,c,d,a,b,c,d] detects period=4.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

