fix: prevent router loop by excluding planning specialists after context gathered
Problem:
Router was looping infinitely: User → Triage → Facilitator → Router → Triage (repeat)
This caused loop detection to trigger and halt workflow with error.

Root Cause:
After Facilitator gathered context, Router's LLM didn't understand that Triage's
job was DONE (one-time planning) and kept routing back to it instead of routing
to a response specialist (chat, summarizer).

Solution:
Added context-aware routing logic in router_specialist._get_available_specialists():
- Detects when 'gathered_context' exists in artifacts
- Removes 'triage_architect' and 'facilitator_specialist' from available specialists
- Forces router to choose a response specialist (chat, summarizer, etc.)

Expected Flow:
BEFORE: User → Triage → Facilitator → Router → Triage → [LOOP DETECTION ERROR]
AFTER:  User → Triage → Facilitator → Router → Chat → End [SUCCESS]

Testing:
Verified with inline test:
- Without gathered_context: All specialists available (including triage)
- With gathered_context: Planning specialists excluded, only response specialists remain

Files Modified:
- app/src/specialists/router_specialist.py (lines 52-65)

