Implement Task 2.6: Refactor FileSpecialist to MCP-only mode
Complete refactor of FileSpecialist to operate exclusively via MCP:
- Removed ToolMessage architecture (no longer processes graph messages)
- Added path validation using pathlib.Path.resolve() and relative_to()
- Implemented 6 MCP service functions:
  * file_exists(path) -> bool
  * read_file(path) -> str
  * write_file(path, content) -> str
  * list_files(path=".") -> List[str]
  * create_directory(path) -> str
  * create_zip(source_path, destination_path) -> str
- Made _execute_logic() a no-op with warning
- Completely rewrote test suite: 39 tests, all passing

Security improvements:
- Path validation prevents directory traversal attacks (../../etc/passwd)
- All operations confined within root_dir (default: ./workspace)
- Defense-in-depth alongside container isolation

FileSpecialist demonstrates the MCP-only pattern: specialists expose
service functions, register them via register_mcp_services(), and
other specialists call them synchronously via mcp_client.call().
This eliminates LLM involvement and routing overhead for deterministic
file operations.

