2025-11-05 15:18:11 -0700
Fix CORE-CHAT-002 state management: Progenitors write only to artifacts
PROBLEM:
Progenitors were returning both "messages" and "artifacts" keys, violating
the LangGraph fan-out/join pattern. This caused:
- 78% token waste in multi-turn conversations (~1600 vs ~900 tokens/turn)
- Broken cross-referencing (progenitors couldn't reference each other's past responses)
- Message pollution (4 messages/turn instead of 2: user, alpha, bravo, synthesizer)

SOLUTION:
Updated ProgenitorAlphaSpecialist and ProgenitorBravoSpecialist to return
ONLY artifacts key, never messages. This follows the critical pattern:
- Parallel nodes (progenitors) write to temporary storage (artifacts)
- Join node (synthesizer) reads artifacts and writes to permanent storage (messages)

IMPACT:
- Multi-turn conversations now properly accumulate 2 messages per turn
- Progenitors can cross-reference each other's responses from history
- Clean separation between parallel execution and message history

FILES CHANGED:
- app/src/specialists/progenitor_alpha_specialist.py: Removed messages key from return
- app/src/specialists/progenitor_bravo_specialist.py: Removed messages key from return

REFERENCES:
- State management pattern documented in DEVELOPERS_GUIDE.md Section 4.7.2
- LangGraph fan-out/join pattern: parallel nodes write artifacts, join writes messages

