Implement Tiered Chat Subgraph with parallel progenitor specialists (ADR CORE-CHAT-002)
Implements multi-perspective chat system using LangGraph fan-out/join pattern:
- ProgenitorAlpha: Analytical perspective specialist
- ProgenitorBravo: Contextual/intuitive perspective specialist
- TieredSynthesizer: Procedural combiner (no LLM) that formats responses

Key architectural features:
- Virtual Coordinator pattern: Router selects "chat_specialist", orchestrator
  intercepts and fans out to parallel progenitors
- Graceful degradation: Works with both, alpha-only, or bravo-only responses
- Efficiency optimization: TieredSynthesizer writes final_user_response.md
  to skip redundant EndSpecialist synthesis (reduces LLM calls from 3 to 2)

Graph wiring changes:
- GraphOrchestrator.route_to_next_specialist() returns str | list[str]
- Array syntax for fan-in: workflow.add_edge(["alpha", "bravo"], "synthesizer")
- Progenitor specialists excluded from router's tool schema (internal to subgraph)

Configuration:
- Added progenitor_alpha_specialist, progenitor_bravo_specialist,
  tiered_synthesizer_specialist to config.yaml
- System auto-enables tiered chat when all three specialists present

Testing:
- 26 new unit tests covering initialization, response generation,
  artifact storage, graceful degradation, and formatting
- All tests passing (8 Alpha, 8 Bravo, 10 TieredSynthesizer)

Implements decisions from:
- ADR CORE-CHAT-002: Tiered Chat Subgraph (Fan-Out)
- ADR CORE-CHAT-002.1: Graceful Degradation Strategy
- ADR CORE-CHAT-002.2: Virtual Coordinator Pattern
- ADR CORE-CHAT-002_FINAL_DECISIONS

