shanevcantwell
you@example.com
2025-11-03 17:00:02 -0700
Fix streaming state accumulation in Gradio UI
Previously, the streaming formatter was capturing only the last specialist's
output delta instead of the full accumulated state. This caused the Gradio UI
to show incomplete JSON state (empty routing_history, turn_count: 0).

The root cause was that each streaming chunk contains only state deltas from
individual specialists. EndSpecialist returns archival_updates which lacks
routing_history and turn_count, so when we captured final_state = node_output
from the last chunk, we lost all the accumulated orchestration state.

This commit implements proper state accumulation following GraphState reducer
semantics:
- Lists (messages, routing_history): Extended using operator.add
- Dicts (artifacts, scratchpad): Merged using operator.ior
- Primitives (turn_count, task_is_complete): Overwritten with latest value

The formatter now maintains accumulated_state throughout the stream and sends
the complete final state to the UI, including routing_history, turn_count,
artifacts, and archive_report.

Fixes: Gradio UI JSON state showing incomplete data
Related: app/src/graph/state.py - GraphState reducer annotations

