ADR-001 Part B: ChatSpecialist implementation complete
This commit implements ChatSpecialist, a foundational conversational
specialist for general Q&A and natural dialogue. It demonstrates the
validated pattern from Part A - new specialists can be added through
config-only changes without modifying router code.

## Implementation

### New Specialist
- `chat_specialist.py`: General-purpose conversational specialist
  - Handles Q&A, explanations, and straightforward dialogue
  - Maintains conversation context across multiple turns
  - Gracefully handles LLM failures with fallback messages
  - Marks tasks as complete (self-contained responses)
  - Adds responses to scratchpad for final synthesis

### Prompt File
- `chat_prompt.md`: System instructions for conversational behavior
  - Emphasizes clarity, accuracy, and helpfulness
  - Defines scope (what ChatSpecialist should/shouldn't do)
  - Acknowledges it's part of a larger multi-agent system

### Configuration
- `config.yaml`: Registered in "General & Fallback" section
  - Clear description enables router to route appropriately
  - Standard LLM type with prompt file binding
- `user_settings.yaml.example`: Fixed pre-existing bugs + added bindings
  - Fixed duplicate api_identifier in gemini_flash definition
  - Fixed comment (Procedural → Hybrid for OpenInterpreter/EndSpecialist)
  - Added chat_specialist and end_specialist bindings

### Tests
- `test_chat_specialist.py`: Comprehensive test suite (6 tests)
  - ✓ Initialization
  - ✓ Simple question processing
  - ✓ Conversation context maintenance
  - ✓ Graceful LLM failure handling
  - ✓ Proper message metadata
  - ✓ Empty message history edge case

## Verification

**Router Discovery**:
- Router discovers ChatSpecialist automatically via config.yaml
- No router code modifications required
- Validates ADR-001 Part A architectural foundation

**Test Results**:
- 6/6 ChatSpecialist tests passing
- 4/4 router discovery tests passing
- All existing unit tests still passing

**Live Demonstration**:
- ChatSpecialist processes user questions successfully
- Router finds ChatSpecialist via dynamic discovery
- Full integration validated in Docker environment

## ADR-001 Status

✅ **Part A** (Architectural Validation): Committed [45e792b]
✅ **Part B** (Specialist Implementation): This commit

ADR-001 is now complete. ChatSpecialist is fully integrated and
ready to handle conversational queries in the workflow.

